# ⚠️ SECURITY WARNING: NEVER COMMIT YOUR .env FILE WITH REAL TOKENS!
# This .env.example file is a template. Copy it to .env and add your real tokens there.
# The .env file is already in .gitignore and will NOT be committed.

# GitHub Personal Access Token (REQUIRED)
# Generate at: https://github.com/settings/tokens
# Required scopes: repo, read:user
# Never commit actual tokens - only use environment variables!
GITHUB_TOKEN=your_github_token_here

# Optional: Enterprise Integration Tokens
# Only needed if you use the integration examples in examples/integrations/

# Slack Bot Token (for Slack integration example)
# Generate at: https://api.slack.com/apps
# Format: xoxb-xxxxxxxxxxxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=your_slack_token_here
# SLACK_CHANNEL_ID=C0123456789

# Jira API Token (for Jira integration example)
# Generate at: https://id.atlassian.com/manage-profile/security/api-tokens
# JIRA_URL=https://your-company.atlassian.net
# JIRA_EMAIL=your-email@company.com
# JIRA_API_TOKEN=your_jira_token_here

# ⚠️ REMINDER: If you accidentally commit a real token:
# 1. IMMEDIATELY revoke it at its source
# 2. Generate a new token
# 3. See .github/TOKEN-EXPOSURE-RESPONSE.md for detailed steps